cyclone.name: ZETA
cyclone.current_location: about 210 miles SE of Cozumel, Mexico
cyclone.trajectory: moving northwest toward the northern Yucatan, then accelerating north-northeast across the Gulf toward the northern Gulf Coast and continuing inland toward the Mid-Atlantic

weather_observation.impacted_coast: Northern Gulf Coast (LA to AL) then inland across the Tennessee Valley and Mid-Atlantic including Chesapeake Bay shoreline
weather_observation.wind: Low (≈3%) chance of sustained tropical-storm-force winds; gusty 25–35 mph winds possible Thursday
weather_observation.storm_surge: None expected for Baltimore’s section of Chesapeake Bay
weather_observation.rainfall: 2–4 inches with isolated 6-inch totals could cause flash and urban flooding Thursday–Friday
weather_observation.other_hazards: Isolated tornadoes and brief marine squalls possible as remnant low passes
